verses.text_plain: Israel is an empty vine, he bringeth forth fruit unto himself: according to the multitude of his fruit he hath increased the altars; according to the goodness of his land they have made goodly images.
verses.verse_html:
1Israel is an empty vine, he bringeth forth fruit unto himself: according to the multitude of his fruit he hath increased the altars; according to the goodness of his land they have made goodly images. ▼
▼ an…: or, a vine emptying the fruit which it giveth
 , ▼
▼ images: Heb. statues, or, standing images

tokens.text: unto himself: according to the multitude

footnotes.body_text: ▼ an…: or, a vine emptying the fruit which it giveth
footnotes.body_html: ▼ an…: or, a vine emptying the fruit which it giveth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ images: Heb. statues, or, standing images
footnotes.body_html: ▼ images: Heb. statues, or, standing images

verses.text_plain: Their heart is divided; now shall they be found faulty: he shall break down their altars, he shall spoil their images.
verses.verse_html:
2Their heart is divided; now shall they be found faulty: he shall break down their altars, he shall spoil their images. ▼
▼ Their heart…: or, He hath divided their heart
 , ▼
▼ break…: Heb. behead
 , ▼
▼ images: Heb. statues, or, standing images

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Their heart…: or, He hath divided their heart

verses.text_plain: For now they shall say, We have no king, because we feared not the Lord; what then should a king do to us?
verses.verse_html: 3For now they shall say, We have no king, because we feared not the Lord; what then should a king do to us?

verses.text_plain: They have spoken words, swearing falsely in making a covenant: thus judgment springeth up as hemlock in the furrows of the field.
verses.verse_html: 4They have spoken words, swearing falsely in making a covenant: thus judgment springeth up as hemlock in the furrows of the field.

verses.text_plain: The inhabitants of Samaria shall fear because of the calves of Beth–aven: for the people thereof shall mourn over it, and the priests thereof that rejoiced on it, for the glory thereof, because it is departed from it.
verses.verse_html:
5The inhabitants of Samaria shall fear because of the calves of Beth–aven: for the people thereof shall mourn over it, and the priests thereof that rejoiced on it, for the glory thereof, because it is departed from it. ▼
▼ the priests…: or, Chemarim

footnotes.body_html: ▼ the priests…: or, Chemarim

verses.text_plain: It shall be also carried unto Assyria for a present to king Jareb: Ephraim shall receive shame, and Israel shall be ashamed of his own counsel.
verses.verse_html: 6It shall be also carried unto Assyria for a present to king Jareb: Ephraim shall receive shame, and Israel shall be ashamed of his own counsel.

verses.text_plain: As for Samaria, her king is cut off as the foam upon the water.
verses.verse_html:
7As for Samaria, her king is cut off as the foam upon the water. ▼
▼ the water: Heb. the face of the water

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the water: Heb. the face of the water
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the water: Heb. the face of the water

verses.text_plain: The high places also of Aven, the sin of Israel, shall be destroyed: the thorn and the thistle shall come up on their altars; and they shall say to the mountains, Cover us; and to the hills, Fall on us.
verses.verse_html: 8The high places also of Aven, the sin of Israel, shall be destroyed: the thorn and the thistle shall come up on their altars; and they shall say to the mountains, Cover us; and to the hills, Fall on us.

verses.text_plain: O Israel, thou hast sinned from the days of Gibeah: there they stood: the battle in Gibeah against the children of iniquity did not overtake them.
verses.verse_html: 9O Israel, thou hast sinned from the days of Gibeah: there they stood: the battle in Gibeah against the children of iniquity did not overtake them.

verses.text_plain: It is in my desire that I should chastise them; and the people shall be gathered against them, when they shall bind themselves in their two furrows.
verses.verse_html:
10It is in my desire that I should chastise them; and the people shall be gathered against them, when they shall bind themselves in their two furrows. ▼
▼ when…: or, when I shall bind them for their two transgressions, or, in their two habitations

tokens.text: against them, when they shall bind

footnotes.body_text: ▼ when…: or, when I shall bind them for their two transgressions, or, in their two habitations
footnotes.body_html: ▼ when…: or, when I shall bind them for their two transgressions, or, in their two habitations

verses.text_plain: And Ephraim is as an heifer that is taught, and loveth to tread out the corn; but I passed over upon her fair neck: I will make Ephraim to ride; Judah shall plow, and Jacob shall break his clods.
verses.verse_html:
11And Ephraim is as an heifer that is taught, and loveth to tread out the corn; but I passed over upon her fair neck: I will make Ephraim to ride; Judah shall plow, and Jacob shall break his clods. ▼
▼ her…: Heb. the beauty of her neck

footnotes.body_text: ▼ her…: Heb. the beauty of her neck
footnotes.body_html: ▼ her…: Heb. the beauty of her neck

verses.text_plain: Sow to yourselves in righteousness, reap in mercy; break up your fallow ground: for it is time to seek the Lord, till he come and rain righteousness upon you.
verses.verse_html: 12Sow to yourselves in righteousness, reap in mercy; break up your fallow ground: for it is time to seek the Lord, till he come and rain righteousness upon you.

verses.text_plain: Ye have plowed wickedness, ye have reaped iniquity; ye have eaten the fruit of lies: because thou didst trust in thy way, in the multitude of thy mighty men.
verses.verse_html: 13Ye have plowed wickedness, ye have reaped iniquity; ye have eaten the fruit of lies: because thou didst trust in thy way, in the multitude of thy mighty men.

verses.text_plain: Therefore shall a tumult arise among thy people, and all thy fortresses shall be spoiled, as Shalman spoiled Beth–arbel in the day of battle: the mother was dashed in pieces upon her children.
verses.verse_html: 14Therefore shall a tumult arise among thy people, and all thy fortresses shall be spoiled, as Shalman spoiled Beth–arbel in the day of battle: the mother was dashed in pieces upon her children.

verses.text_plain: So shall Beth–el do unto you because of your great wickedness: in a morning shall the king of Israel utterly be cut off.
verses.verse_html:
15So shall Beth–el do unto you because of your great wickedness: in a morning shall the king of Israel utterly be cut off. ▼
▼ your…: Heb. the evil of your evil

footnotes.body_text: ▼ your…: Heb. the evil of your evil
footnotes.body_html: ▼ your…: Heb. the evil of your evil
